sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K624033
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part, minC, is known as a cell division inhibitor. It was first submitted by 2010 Warsaw iGEM team.(http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K299806) However, there was a PstI site in the middle of the sequence, which makes it hard to do biobrick assembly. We designed primers to remove the site with a synonymous substitution.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yi-Hong Liou
